  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As outlined in the spec, a node should delay processing of the attestation until the next slot. We currently violate that check by discarding the attestation instead of keeping it around. Opening this issue to track it\r\n\r\nReference: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.11.1/specs/phase0/fork-choice.md#on_attestation\r\n\r\n```python\r\n    # Attestations can only affect the fork choice of subsequent slots.\r\n    # Delay consideration in the fork choice until their slot is in the past.\r\n    assert get_current_slot(store) >= attestation.data.slot + 1\r\n```",
